analysis: The documents all pertain to the revocation of previous executive orders that had withdrawn public lands from general access, followed by a re-opening of these lands for homesteading and desert land entry, specifically prioritizing qualified ex-service men for a 91-day period. This action is consistently linked to Public Resolution 85, approved June 12, 1930, which grants service recognition to these veterans. The documents span multiple states including Colorado, Wyoming, California, Nevada, New Mexico, Arkansas and Montana.
title: Land Re-Opening for Veterans
